footprints.title: Asakusa Shrine
footprints.description: The oldest Buddhist temple. Very quiet, very respectful, very clean. Skip the selfie.

footprints.title: Top of Park Hyatt
footprints.description: This is where they shot that scene in Lost in Translation. It's, extremely, high up.

footprints.title: Meiji Shrine
footprints.description: One of the lesser visited temples, set in a forest of Gingko trees. Take your trash with you!

footprints.title: Wasteland Thrift Shop
footprints.description: Soak in the glory that is the Haight-Ashbury, and get yourself an outfit to blend in.

footprints.title: The Booksmith
footprints.description: Amazing book store (next to an amazing sock shop), where the people who work there write little notes and descriptions on all the books.

footprints.title: Cha Cha Cha
footprints.description: Best Sangria in the city, really cool decor, and so delicious. Good for bigger groups too!

footprints.title: Murio's Trophy Room
footprints.description: Dogs allowed, a pool table, and they'll let you play your own music if you ask Nick nicely :)

footprints.title: Venice Beach Shopping
footprints.Address: Abbot Kinney Blvd, Los Angeles CA
footprints.description: If Rodeo Drive isn't your scene, Venice beach might be. Still has those LA prices tho;)

footprints.title: Griffith Observatory
footprints.Address: 2800 E Observatory Road, Los Angeles CA
footprints.description: Sweeping views of LA and some beautiful architecture to go along with it.

footprints.title: Runyon Canyon Park
footprints.Address: 2000 N Fuller Boulevard, Los Angeles CA
footprints.description: Get your movement in for the day! Fun and easy trail and great people watching. Dogs allowed too!

footprints.title: Perch
footprints.Address: 448 S Hill Street, Los Angeles CA
footprints.description: French rooftop bistro, three of the best words you can hear when it comes to food. Unique vibe and great food.

footprints.title: Chez Clarisse
footprints.description: Grilled tilapia, half fried plantain/half acheke side, a star beer, and 90s music videos. Marry me.

footprints.title: James Town Lighthouse
footprints.description: A steep climb and worth the view of all of Accra and the fishing boats. Nobody fishes on Tuesdays tho.

footprints.title: Diagon Alley (Leadenhall Market)
footprints.description: The market that inspired Diagon Alley. Still waiting on my Hogwarts letter tho

footprints.title: Camden Market
footprints.description: There are cars coming out of the building and carmelized nuts sold on the street. Quite a mix.

footprints.title: Old Spitalfields Market
footprints.description: Artists, creatives, lined with curry houses. Quirky and Victorian all at once. Plus the name is hilarious.

footprints.title: Diagon Alley (Leadenhall Market)
footprints.description: The market that inspired Diagon Alley. Still waiting on my Hogwarts letter tho

footprints.title: Platform 9 and 3/4
footprints.description: Don't wait in the line to take a photo. Take a photo of the line.

footprints.title: Blind Pig
footprints.description: Butterbeer!! Not really buttery or beer-y...pretty sure it's all sugar. Don't care.

footprints.title: Falling Shopper
footprints.description: It might take you a while to find, get ready to wander.

footprints.title: Always Fall
footprints.description: The address is vague for a reason. #Banksy

footprints.title: Cash Machine
footprints.description: Makes you rethink all that shopping you did yesterday. And good luck finding it.
